    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "CSS Errors"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Errors in CSS can lead to unexpected behavior or styles not being applied correctly. This page shows common CSS mistakes and how to avoid them."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Missing Semicolons"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Forgetting a semicolon at the end of a property declaration can break the style rule."
    },
    {
      "type": "example",
      "description": "",
      "codes": [
        {
          "language": "unknown",
          "code": ".bad {\n  color: red\n  background-color: yellow;\n}"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Invalid Property Names"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Using a property name that does not exist will simply be ignored by the browser."
    },
    {
      "type": "example",
      "description": "",
      "codes": [
        {
          "language": "unknown",
          "code": ".bad {\n  colr: blue;\n  font-size: 16px;\n}"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Invalid Values"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Correct properties but invalid values will also be ignored."
    },
    {
      "type": "example",
      "description": "",
      "codes": [
        {
          "language": "unknown",
          "code": ".bad {\n  width: -100px;\n  color: green;\n}"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Unclosed Braces"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "If you forget to close a brace }, the entire rule may be ignored."
    },
    {
      "type": "example",
      "description": "",
      "codes": [
        {
          "language": "unknown",
          "code": ".bad {\n  padding: 20px;\n  margin: 10px;"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Extra Colons or Braces"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Typos like extra colons or misplaced braces can cause rules to break."
    },
    {
      "type": "example",
      "description": "",
      "codes": [
        {
          "language": "unknown",
          "code": ".bad {\n  color:: blue;\n}"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Tips to Avoid CSS Errors"
    },
    {
      "type": "other",
      "text": "Use a code editor with syntax highlighting.\n  Validate your CSS with a CSS linter or validator.\n  Write CSS in small sections and test frequently."
    },
